1
00:00:35,118 --> 00:00:35,952
Hi, Luisa!

2
00:00:36,036 --> 00:00:39,039
I know you said before
that he's quite a loser.

3
00:00:39,122 --> 00:00:40,415
<i>I'm talking about Angelito.</i>

4
00:00:40,498 --> 00:00:41,916
He invited me to go somewhere.

5
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:43,293
Concert… Do you wanna come?

6
00:00:43,376 --> 00:00:44,544
I'll bring my boyfriend.

7
00:00:44,627 --> 00:00:46,004
Double date.

8
00:00:46,087 --> 00:00:49,007
She's just a police agent
hovering around Mikoy.

9
00:00:49,090 --> 00:00:51,259
<i>After Carlota kills this agent,</i>

10
00:00:51,342 --> 00:00:53,887
<i>I will show her head to Mikoy.</i>

11
00:00:53,970 --> 00:00:54,888
Why are you yelling?

12
00:00:54,971 --> 00:00:58,641
Alex still hasn't arrived
for our morning briefing.

13
00:00:58,725 --> 00:01:00,143
Sianong, check her apartment.

14
00:01:05,315 --> 00:01:06,316
Bok?

15
00:01:09,986 --> 00:01:10,820
Bok!

16
00:01:12,906 --> 00:01:13,740
Bok!

17
00:01:15,950 --> 00:01:17,160
Bok!

18
00:01:25,668 --> 00:01:28,588
Hello, cutie.

19
00:01:31,758 --> 00:01:34,010
- Where's Alex?
- What are you doing here?

20
00:01:37,347 --> 00:01:40,391
Bok, you weren't at the briefing.
You weren't answering my calls.

21
00:01:40,475 --> 00:01:42,018
Of course, I'd be worried.

22
00:01:44,979 --> 00:01:45,814
What is this?

23
00:01:45,897 --> 00:01:46,981
You kidnapped her?

24
00:01:47,899 --> 00:01:49,400
She attacked me last night.

25
00:02:44,789 --> 00:02:45,957
Okay.

26
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:47,542
We need to bring her to HQ.

27
00:02:47,625 --> 00:02:50,086
We interrogate her, by the book.

28
00:02:55,216 --> 00:02:56,050
I know that.

29
00:02:57,969 --> 00:02:58,845
Bok.

30
00:03:08,688 --> 00:03:09,647
Then don't be here.

31
00:03:10,315 --> 00:03:11,316
Get out.

32
00:03:11,399 --> 00:03:12,609
- No.
- So you have deniability.

33
00:03:12,692 --> 00:03:13,776
No.

34
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:15,236
You don't do this!

35
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:16,738
You're not like this.

36
00:03:16,821 --> 00:03:18,281
What's going on with you?

37
00:03:18,364 --> 00:03:20,366
Why is it different with this mission?

38
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:21,492
Huh?

39
00:03:23,036 --> 00:03:24,579
Someone has to do it, Bok.

40
00:03:26,247 --> 00:03:27,457
- No.
- Get out.

41
00:03:27,540 --> 00:03:28,875
You don't break--

42
00:03:29,834 --> 00:03:31,210
Bok, come on!

43
00:03:32,921 --> 00:03:33,880
Bok!

44
00:04:02,617 --> 00:04:03,785
Hello, sir?

45
00:04:04,285 --> 00:04:07,205
<i>Agent Sianong, how's Agent Alex?</i>

46
00:04:07,288 --> 00:04:09,916
She's okay, sir. She just overslept.

47
00:04:09,999 --> 00:04:12,085
She's a bit under the weather, sir.

48
00:04:12,168 --> 00:04:13,711
I'll stay here for now, sir.

49
00:04:13,795 --> 00:04:15,672
Just to make sure she's really okay.

50
00:04:15,755 --> 00:04:18,258
All right, Agent Sianong, stay with her.

51
00:04:18,341 --> 00:04:21,344
Tell her she doesn't need
to report in today.

52
00:04:22,762 --> 00:04:24,681
Yes, sir. Copy that.

53
00:04:46,244 --> 00:04:47,495
Do your worst.

54
00:04:48,329 --> 00:04:50,581
I know people like you by heart.

55
00:04:55,503 --> 00:04:57,714
But you should know better.

56
00:05:18,985 --> 00:05:20,486
Because if not,

57
00:05:20,987 --> 00:05:23,031
let me just tell you…

58
00:05:23,531 --> 00:05:26,534
I've subscribed
to the Miley Cyrus principle.

59
00:05:45,219 --> 00:05:49,182
<i>I need to know why Alex came to see me.</i>
<i>I need to talk to her.</i>

60
00:05:53,102 --> 00:05:54,062
There.

61
00:05:55,146 --> 00:05:57,315
Dial it, Mikoy.

62
00:05:57,815 --> 00:06:00,735
So we can finally find out your secret.

63
00:06:01,903 --> 00:06:03,488
Ring, ring.

64
00:06:04,155 --> 00:06:06,032
Mikoy.

65
00:06:09,494 --> 00:06:10,328
Let's go.

66
00:06:14,874 --> 00:06:16,959
From now on, the phone we gave you…

67
00:06:17,043 --> 00:06:18,461
Don't use it anymore.

68
00:06:18,544 --> 00:06:20,046
We've got you covered. We'll contact you.

69
00:06:20,129 --> 00:06:21,255
We'll find a way.

70
00:06:47,323 --> 00:06:49,200
I'll get you at the right time.

71
00:06:57,208 --> 00:06:58,334
Double date.

72
00:06:58,835 --> 00:07:01,420
With Angelito and Luisa Mae.

73
00:07:01,504 --> 00:07:03,464
Really, Sofie?

74
00:07:05,049 --> 00:07:06,509
Oh, come on!

75
00:07:07,343 --> 00:07:08,636
You know, Sofie,

76
00:07:09,137 --> 00:07:10,721
you're smart.

77
00:07:10,805 --> 00:07:12,890
But you know what you did?

78
00:07:12,974 --> 00:07:14,642
That wasn't smart at all.

79
00:07:14,725 --> 00:07:16,477
All you say is yes

80
00:07:16,561 --> 00:07:17,812
and rushing in.

81
00:07:17,895 --> 00:07:19,772
And now what?

82
00:07:20,273 --> 00:07:21,357
Nothing!

83
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:24,902
Oh, Sofie…

84
00:07:33,703 --> 00:07:35,121
Hi, sir.

85
00:07:36,414 --> 00:07:38,708
Instead of just standing there,

86
00:07:38,791 --> 00:07:41,252
why don't you join me?

87
00:07:41,752 --> 00:07:43,296
Just pretend to be my boyfriend.

88
00:07:43,379 --> 00:07:45,548
You know, this is just one time.

89
00:07:47,341 --> 00:07:49,093
You don't need to talk.

90
00:07:49,177 --> 00:07:52,263
I'll handle the whole love story.

91
00:07:52,346 --> 00:07:55,224
Where we met, where we dated.

92
00:07:55,725 --> 00:07:57,935
And I'll even explain your personality.

93
00:07:58,019 --> 00:07:59,437
You're the quiet type.

94
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:01,522
I'm the extrovert.

95
00:08:01,606 --> 00:08:02,565
That's why we're a perfect match.

96
00:08:02,648 --> 00:08:03,483
Deal?

97
00:08:03,566 --> 00:08:06,068
Come on, just agree
to have a date with me.

98
00:08:06,694 --> 00:08:07,904
- Sofie.
- You'll be my date.

99
00:08:08,821 --> 00:08:10,114
What are you doing?

100
00:08:10,615 --> 00:08:12,408
You're even involving the standee.

101
00:08:25,755 --> 00:08:27,798
Stop. Freeze.

102
00:08:29,967 --> 00:08:30,927
I said freeze!

103
00:08:37,391 --> 00:08:38,976
VERTEX
GLOBAL

104
00:08:56,786 --> 00:08:59,830
I've been calling her for a while now,
but she's not answering.

105
00:09:08,297 --> 00:09:11,092
And she hasn't ended up
in a dangerous situation.

106
00:09:15,805 --> 00:09:16,806
Why?

107
00:09:31,904 --> 00:09:33,239
Who are you?

108
00:09:33,322 --> 00:09:36,200
You're talking too much.
Just put your hands up.

109
00:09:41,789 --> 00:09:43,124
Alex, what are you saying?

110
00:09:43,874 --> 00:09:45,459
I said let her go.

111
00:09:45,543 --> 00:09:46,711
Release her now.

112
00:09:46,794 --> 00:09:48,838
And that's an order, Agent Sianong.

113
00:09:51,132 --> 00:09:52,508
Bye, cutie.

114
00:10:16,365 --> 00:10:18,284
Compared to men, right?

115
00:10:18,367 --> 00:10:20,578
Women really are at a disadvantage.

116
00:10:28,127 --> 00:10:29,462
Try this.

117
00:10:29,545 --> 00:10:31,797
A bit weird, but it's good.

118
00:10:40,014 --> 00:10:42,266
- It is good!
- I told you.

119
00:10:43,351 --> 00:10:44,727
By the way, sir.

120
00:10:45,478 --> 00:10:47,271
Chiara mentioned

121
00:10:47,355 --> 00:10:49,398
that Carlota is your chihuahua.

122
00:10:52,026 --> 00:10:53,527
Why would she say that?

123
00:10:56,364 --> 00:10:57,865
My daughter…

124
00:10:57,948 --> 00:11:00,368
She has a way with words, you know.

125
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:02,286
Sometimes…

126
00:11:02,828 --> 00:11:04,705
her imagination goes too far.

127
00:11:17,968 --> 00:11:19,970
Is Carlota here because

128
00:11:20,554 --> 00:11:22,306
you want someone to watch over me?

129
00:11:24,225 --> 00:11:25,142
Why, sir?

130
00:11:25,768 --> 00:11:29,271
Am I doing anything here at Vertex
that you don't approve of?

131
00:11:32,817 --> 00:11:34,443
Is that why you're having me watched?

132
00:11:48,374 --> 00:11:51,168
What are you thinking, dear?

133
00:11:55,631 --> 00:11:56,841
It's Mikoy.

134
00:11:58,801 --> 00:12:00,469
Something is still off.

135
00:12:01,929 --> 00:12:04,807
The other night, he woke up screaming,

136
00:12:04,890 --> 00:12:06,976
drenched in sweat,

137
00:12:07,059 --> 00:12:09,478
but he wouldn't talk to me about it.

138
00:12:10,271 --> 00:12:12,106
He was so dismissive.

139
00:12:12,189 --> 00:12:14,525
He said it was just a dream.

140
00:12:18,487 --> 00:12:21,449
I can clearly see it's affecting him.

141
00:12:23,325 --> 00:12:24,827
I'm worried, Mama.

142
00:12:26,704 --> 00:12:28,789
That's just how men are.

143
00:12:29,373 --> 00:12:31,083
They say, "I'm fine,"

144
00:12:31,167 --> 00:12:32,626
even when they're not.

145
00:12:35,045 --> 00:12:36,422
Dear, I think

146
00:12:37,506 --> 00:12:41,093
there's something worse
you should be worried about.

147
00:12:43,429 --> 00:12:45,681
Not his nightmares.

148
00:12:45,764 --> 00:12:49,435
Not even his silence.

149
00:12:55,232 --> 00:12:56,984
Your father found out

150
00:12:58,110 --> 00:12:59,820
that there are agents following Mikoy.

151
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:15,503
So I think I can handle
anything, Uncle Vik.

152
00:13:31,769 --> 00:13:34,146
Like what, Uncle Vik?

153
00:13:35,606 --> 00:13:37,399
Is there something I should know?

154
00:14:15,896 --> 00:14:16,981
So…

155
00:14:18,732 --> 00:14:21,861
he's investigating our family
through Mikoy.

156
00:14:22,903 --> 00:14:24,405
Are you sure?

157
00:14:25,406 --> 00:14:26,657
Well…

158
00:14:27,157 --> 00:14:28,450
You know your father.

159
00:14:29,034 --> 00:14:30,744
He has so many theories.

160
00:14:31,495 --> 00:14:33,622
Of course, he overthinks.

161
00:14:34,957 --> 00:14:36,667
But you know our situation, dear.

162
00:14:37,251 --> 00:14:38,836
It pays to overthink.

163
00:14:40,838 --> 00:14:41,755
And of course,

164
00:14:42,339 --> 00:14:45,384
it's your father's responsibility
to worry about us.

165
00:14:46,343 --> 00:14:47,469
So…

166
00:14:48,429 --> 00:14:50,764
we need to keep an eye on Mikoy.

167
00:14:52,224 --> 00:14:53,642
Better yet, dear…

168
00:14:54,768 --> 00:14:58,105
Maybe it's time to tell him the truth.

169
00:15:11,118 --> 00:15:12,578
Why did you let her go?

170
00:15:34,308 --> 00:15:36,226
But what did you do?

171
00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:44,360
That's dereliction of duty!

172
00:15:47,029 --> 00:15:49,782
You let La Fornarina go.

173
00:15:50,366 --> 00:15:53,369
- She is not La Fornarina.
- Fine.

174
00:15:54,036 --> 00:15:54,954
Then how?

175
00:15:55,621 --> 00:15:57,539
La Fornarina is left-handed.

176
00:16:00,542 --> 00:16:01,752
What are you doing?

177
00:16:03,504 --> 00:16:05,130
Freeing you.

178
00:16:05,214 --> 00:16:06,340
You're no use to me.

179
00:16:16,809 --> 00:16:18,352
I have the weapon.

180
00:16:18,852 --> 00:16:20,104
You're at a disadvantage.

181
00:16:26,443 --> 00:16:27,528
Why don't you try?

182
00:17:11,071 --> 00:17:12,948
I told you we're not on the same level.

183
00:17:22,291 --> 00:17:23,625
If you let me walk out of here,

184
00:17:23,709 --> 00:17:25,502
I'll come back for you,

185
00:17:25,586 --> 00:17:28,547
and I'll make sure I kill you.

186
00:17:34,428 --> 00:17:36,180
What's so funny?

187
00:17:52,362 --> 00:17:54,239
What do you think he'll do to you?

188
00:17:56,033 --> 00:17:58,619
He might even suspect
that you're working with us

189
00:17:58,702 --> 00:18:00,537
because I let you go.

190
00:18:00,621 --> 00:18:02,289
So I will give you an option.

191
00:18:03,457 --> 00:18:05,751
Work with me, and I'll
protect you from Viktor.

192
00:18:15,260 --> 00:18:17,012
I can handle my own battles.

193
00:18:22,392 --> 00:18:23,852
That's your decision.

194
00:18:23,936 --> 00:18:25,395
Up to you.

195
00:18:37,908 --> 00:18:40,452
You're playing
a very dangerous game, Alex.

196
00:18:52,923 --> 00:18:56,343
Sometimes, we need
to think outside the box.

197
00:19:08,772 --> 00:19:10,440
Why did you even say that?

198
00:19:10,941 --> 00:19:12,526
You don't even have a boyfriend.

199
00:19:13,026 --> 00:19:13,861
Ouch.

200
00:19:13,944 --> 00:19:16,280
Did you really have
to announce I'm single?

201
00:19:16,905 --> 00:19:18,490
Okay, that's not what I meant.

202
00:19:18,574 --> 00:19:19,825
Sorry.

203
00:19:20,826 --> 00:19:21,827
Let's do this instead.

204
00:19:23,370 --> 00:19:24,329
I'll be your date.

205
00:19:26,999 --> 00:19:27,833
Yes.

206
00:19:27,916 --> 00:19:29,293
Are you serious?

207
00:19:29,376 --> 00:19:30,919
You're volunteering?

208
00:19:31,003 --> 00:19:32,254
I'm serious, for real.

209
00:19:32,337 --> 00:19:33,213
Limited time only.

210
00:19:33,297 --> 00:19:35,340
If I were you, I'd take the offer, Sofie.

211
00:19:36,008 --> 00:19:38,177
And honestly, it'd be sad
if you showed up without a date

212
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:39,928
for the double date you agreed to.

213
00:19:41,388 --> 00:19:43,807
Fair point.

214
00:19:45,225 --> 00:19:46,602
But let me ask you something.

215
00:19:47,269 --> 00:19:49,062
Why are you volunteering
to be my boyfriend?

216
00:19:49,146 --> 00:19:50,522
Fake boyfriend.

217
00:19:50,606 --> 00:19:53,192
Okay, fine, fake boyfriend.

218
00:19:53,275 --> 00:19:54,610
But still.

219
00:19:54,693 --> 00:19:57,321
Why are you really doing this?

220
00:19:57,404 --> 00:19:59,865
What is it? Do you have
too much free time?

221
00:19:59,948 --> 00:20:01,366
Are you bored?

222
00:20:02,409 --> 00:20:04,703
Oh, I know this type.

223
00:20:06,246 --> 00:20:07,831
You like me, don't you?

224
00:20:07,915 --> 00:20:09,958
You secretly like me,

225
00:20:10,042 --> 00:20:11,960
and you're hoping that one day

226
00:20:12,044 --> 00:20:13,587
I'll notice you.

227
00:20:13,670 --> 00:20:15,839
Oh, wow. Your style is terrible.

228
00:20:17,716 --> 00:20:19,843
You're really annoying, you know that?

229
00:20:19,927 --> 00:20:22,095
Simple. If you don't want to, then don't.

230
00:20:23,472 --> 00:20:25,599
Hey, Laurence. Just kidding.

231
00:20:25,682 --> 00:20:27,142
Come on.

232
00:20:29,144 --> 00:20:30,270
Sorry.

233
00:20:30,354 --> 00:20:31,772
It's just a joke.

234
00:20:31,855 --> 00:20:33,815
Don't be so sensitive.

235
00:20:35,025 --> 00:20:37,027
Come on. Let's make up.

236
00:20:37,903 --> 00:20:40,447
Do you want to know
why I volunteered to be your date?

237
00:20:40,530 --> 00:20:43,200
Huh? But why?

238
00:20:49,456 --> 00:20:50,874
Because I like you.

239
00:21:01,677 --> 00:21:04,012
Your face looks like
you just won the lottery.

240
00:21:07,516 --> 00:21:09,893
Hey. Don't tell me you're sulking.

241
00:21:11,812 --> 00:21:12,646
Sulking!

242
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:27,035
Why are you still alive?

243
00:21:27,744 --> 00:21:29,288
I escaped, sir.

244
00:21:29,871 --> 00:21:31,248
But I'm injured.

245
00:22:28,847 --> 00:22:30,140
Marie.

246
00:22:32,476 --> 00:22:36,146
Is this the complete manpower list
of our drivers?

247
00:22:36,229 --> 00:22:38,398
Yes, sir. That's what I already
gave Ma'am Carlota.

248
00:22:38,482 --> 00:22:39,941
That's what she requested.

249
00:22:41,276 --> 00:22:42,319
But…

250
00:22:44,154 --> 00:22:45,489
It feels like something's missing.

251
00:22:46,698 --> 00:22:47,991
Can I see, sir?

252
00:22:48,617 --> 00:22:49,451
Oh.

253
00:22:50,869 --> 00:22:52,788
Yes, it seems so, sir.

254
00:22:52,871 --> 00:22:55,290
Maybe it got missed in the photocopy, sir.

255
00:23:03,381 --> 00:23:04,341
Right away, sir.

256
00:23:38,583 --> 00:23:39,751
Morning, sir.

257
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:43,588
Someone is waiting for you.

258
00:24:06,987 --> 00:24:09,114
Here, sir. It's complete now.

259
00:24:12,075 --> 00:24:13,118
Hmm…

260
00:24:15,287 --> 00:24:16,163
This one.

261
00:24:17,372 --> 00:24:19,249
Jose Cuenca.

262
00:24:20,167 --> 00:24:22,878
Late. Late again.

263
00:24:22,961 --> 00:24:24,337
Late once more.

264
00:24:26,214 --> 00:24:27,465
Over and over again.

265
00:24:27,966 --> 00:24:30,844
These drivers are always delayed
with deliveries.

266
00:24:30,927 --> 00:24:32,137
But it feels like…

267
00:24:33,305 --> 00:24:34,556
like nothing happens.

268
00:24:35,182 --> 00:24:36,850
There is no sign of reprimand.

269
00:24:45,817 --> 00:24:46,985
Sir, I don't know.

270
00:24:49,196 --> 00:24:50,405
Okay, you can go.

271
00:24:50,488 --> 00:24:51,656
Okay, sir.

272
00:24:54,034 --> 00:24:56,828
<i>I need to report this to Agent Alex.</i>

273
00:25:08,965 --> 00:25:10,592
Gotta make that call, buddy.

274
00:25:11,384 --> 00:25:12,219
Let's go.

275
00:25:19,351 --> 00:25:20,310
There it is.

276
00:25:21,478 --> 00:25:22,687
Keep it going.

277
00:25:24,105 --> 00:25:26,650
I need to know your secrets.

278
00:25:46,628 --> 00:25:47,420
<i>Norberto.</i>

279
00:25:53,009 --> 00:25:54,302
<i>What's the agent's name?</i>

280
00:25:55,720 --> 00:25:57,305
But Mikoy, what are you even doing here?

281
00:26:01,268 --> 00:26:02,519
Come here.

282
